<inglise> COMMISSION DECISION of 22 January 1996 on the application, at the request of Germany, of Article 5 (4) of Council Directive 93/75/EEC concerning minimum requirements for vessels bound for or leaving Community ports and carrying dangerous or polluting goods </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; (miinimumn&otilde;uete kohta, mis k&auml;sitlevad ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu vedavaid laevu, mis suunduvad &uuml;henduse sadamatesse v&otilde;i lahkuvad sealt) artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaldamisest Saksamaa taotlusel 22. jaanuar 1996 </eesti>
<inglise> (Only the German text is authentic) </inglise>
<eesti> (Ainult saksakeelne tekst on autentne) </eesti>
<inglise> (96/127/EC) </inglise>
<eesti> (96/127/E&Uuml;) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 93/75/EEC of 13 September 1993 concerning minimum requirements for vessels bound for or leaving Community ports and carrying dangerous or polluting goods (1), and in particular Article 5 (4) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 13. septembri 1993. aasta direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; miinimumn&otilde;uete kohta, mis k&auml;sitlevad ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu vedavaid laevu, mis suunduvad &uuml;henduse sadamatesse v&otilde;i lahkuvad sealt, eriti selle artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 4 (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to limit the risks of serious accidents at sea and to reduce the resulting damage, Article 5 of Directive 93/75/EEC provides that the operators of the vessels covered by the Directive shall notify the information listed in Annex I thereto to the competent authorities of the Member State concerned; whereas Article 5 (4) authorizes the Member State to exempt regular scheduled services of less than one hour's crossing time from such notification requirement and allows the Commission to agree to a reasonable extension of this period on request from a Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: v&auml;hendamaks t&otilde;siste &otilde;nnestuste ohtu merel ning sellest tulenevat kahju on direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artiklis 5 s&auml;testatud, et direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud laevade kasutajad esitavad selle I lisas loetletud teabe asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele; artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 4 lubatakse liikmesriigil vabastada sellest teatamisn&otilde;udest alla tunnise &uuml;les&otilde;iduajaga regulaarliinid ning v&otilde;imaldatakse komisjonil n&otilde;ustuda liikmesriigi taotlusel selle aja m&otilde;istliku pikendamisega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, by communication of 12 April 1994, the Federal Republic of Germany asked the Commission to agree to an extension of this period for the services operated between the ports of Norddeich and Juist, Norddeich and Baltrum, and Emden and Borkum (East Frisia), which have crossing times respectively of 1 hour 30 minutes, 2 hours, and 2 hours and 15 minutes; </inglise>
<eesti> 12. aprilli 1994. aasta teatises palus Saksamaa Liitvabariik komisjonil n&otilde;ustuda selle aja pikendamisega Norddeichi ja Juisti, Norddeichi ja Baltrumi ning Emdeni ja Borkumi (Ida-Friisi saared) sadama vahelise liikluse puhul, kus &uuml;les&otilde;iduajad on vastavalt 1 tund ja 30 minutit, 2 tundi ning 2 tundi ja 15 minutit; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas those services are operated as regular scheduled services between the ports concerned, on a fixed timetable; </inglise>
<eesti> need liinid toimivad regulaarliinidena kindla s&otilde;iduplaani alusel k&otilde;nealuste sadamate vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the services are operated in sheltered sea areas close to the coastline and with favourable mean maritime weather conditions; whereas the waters in which the vessels operate are duly buoyed and are marked for the attention of navigators in the relevant nautical documents; whereas the vessels concerned are required to comply with the local navigation rules and are in constant contact, in particular by radio, with the sea traffic management centre ashore; </inglise>
<eesti> liinid toimivad kaitstud merealal ranniku l&auml;hedal ning mereilmastikutingimused on &uuml;ldiselt soodsad; veed, kus laevad s&otilde;idavad, on kohaselt poidega m&auml;rgistatud ning meres&otilde;itjate t&auml;helepanu juhitakse sellele kohastes meredokumentides; k&otilde;nealused laevad peavad t&auml;itma kohalikke meres&otilde;idureegleid ning olema kaldal asuva mereliikluse juhtimiskeskusega pidevas &uuml;henduses, eriti raadio kaudu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas only small quantities of dangerous or polluting goods are carried on board; whereas the risk to the environment is therefore minimal; </inglise>
<eesti> laevadel veetakse ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu ainult v&auml;ikestes kogustes; keskkonna ohustamise risk on seet&otilde;ttu minimaalne; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the information referred to in Annex I to Directive 93/75/EEC concerning the kind of cargo carried is available to the captain and the operator of the vessels concerned throughout the crossing and can at any time be transmitted to the competent authorities on request; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 93//5/EM&Uuml; I lisas osutatud teave veetava lasti laadi kohta on k&otilde;nealuste laevade kaptenitelt ja kasutajatelt k&auml;ttesaadav kogu &uuml;les&otilde;idu jooksul ning taotluse korral saab seda igal ajal esitada p&auml;devatele ametiasutustele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the circumstances, it is justifiable to accept the request from Germany to exempt the regular scheduled services referred to above from the application of Article 5 (2) and (3) of Directive 93/75/EEC, </inglise>
<eesti> antud asjaoludel on n&otilde;ustumine Saksamaa taotlusega vabastada eespool nimetatud regulaarliinid direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaldamisest p&otilde;hjendatud, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Germany is hereby authorized to exempt the following regular scheduled services: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga lubatakse Saksamaal vabastada j&auml;rgmised regulaarliinid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) between Norddeich and Juist; </inglise>
<eesti> a) Norddeichi ja Juisti vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) between Norddeich and Baltrum; and </inglise>
<eesti> b) Norddeichi ja Baltrumi vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) between Emden and Borkum </inglise>
<eesti> c) Emdeni ja Borkumi vahel </eesti>
<inglise> from the application of Article 5 (2) and (3) of Directive 93/75/EEC, provided that the following requirements are met: </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaldamisest, kui j&auml;rgmised n&otilde;uded on t&auml;idetud: </eesti>
<inglise> - the waters in which the services covered by this Decision operate shall be duly buoyed and marked for the attention of navigators in the relevant nautical documents, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&auml;esoleva otsusega h&otilde;lmatud liiklus toimub vetes, mis on kohaselt poidega m&auml;rgistatud ning meres&otilde;itjate t&auml;helepanu juhitakse sellele kohastes meredokumentides, </eesti>
<inglise> - the vessels concerned shall be required to comply with the local navigation rules, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;nealustelt laevadelt n&otilde;utakse kohalike meres&otilde;idureeglite t&auml;itmist, </eesti>
<inglise> - the vessels concerned shall be required to keep in constant contact, in particular by radio links, with the competent sea traffic service, </inglise>
<eesti> -k&otilde;nealustelt laevadelt n&otilde;utakse p&auml;deva mereliiklustalitusega pidevat &uuml;hendusepidamist, eriti raadioside kaudu, </eesti>
<inglise> - only small quantities of dangerous or polluting goods, within the meaning of Directive 93/75/EEC, shall be carried on board, </inglise>
<eesti> - laevadel veetakse ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu ainult v&auml;ikeses koguses direktiivi 93//5EM&Uuml; t&auml;henduses, </eesti>
<inglise> - the information referred to in Annex I to Directive 93/75/EEC shall be available to the operators and captains of the vessel concerned throughout the crossing and shall at any time be transmissible to the authorities of the Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> - direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; I lisas osutatud teave on k&otilde;nealuse laeva kasutajatelt ja kaptenitelt k&auml;ttesaadav kogu &uuml;les&otilde;idu jooksul ning seda saab igal ajal esitada liikmesriigi ametiasutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Federal Republic of Germany. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud Saksamaa Liitvabariigile. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 22 January 1996. </inglise>
